Hmmm... let me just say that given the current status of physics it is highly unlikely that you will ever naturally fly no matter how much you believe you can. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  The physical world limits what we can probably do under certain conditions.<br>
<br>
Concerning your assertions over &quot;time&quot; and &quot;free will&quot; I fail to see how you are connecting the two. Perhaps you could explain the relevance of time with free will?<br>
<br>
&quot;Free will is the freedom to make a choice&quot; and choice in its &quot;naturalistic sense is dependent upon the 'natural' variable at hand&quot; you say, but then you go on to say that is incorrect because we have &quot;free will with regards to what we BELIEVE&quot;. You then say we &quot;...CAN believe anything we so choose.&quot; I am not really following your line of reasoning. Why isn't choice dependant upon the &quot;natural variable at hand&quot; as you put it?<br>
<br>
Also, while we may be able to believe anything we so choose I fail to understand how that ties into the Free Will argument. Are you saying that because I can freely believe the statement &quot;X is a unicorn&quot; is true that I have free will? But I can't believe &quot;X is a unicorn&quot; is true unless I have good reason for such a belief. In other words, there are conditions that must first arise causing my belief. If we want to say that my belief that the statement is true has no prior conditions causing my belief then we are saying my belief is irrational. In other words we are saying I have no reasons to believe the statement to be true or false. This is the point I was making to Triff; it is not coherent to claim that I could have done otherwise (or chose otherwise). Certain conditions must be in place for us to choose X or Y. To say that I could have chosen otherwise is just to say that a different set of conditions were in place causing my choice. Choice is a very short leash. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Lurikeen Mali'Kyre<BR>
